This repository uses a strict protected-branch workflow to ensure that code cannot change without explicit review and approval.

Contribution Rules
	â€¢	All changes must be submitted via a pull request (PR).
	â€¢	The main branch is protected â€” no one can push to it directly.
	â€¢	All PRs require approval from the project maintainer before they can be merged.
	â€¢	At this time, the only maintainer with merge permissions is Gavin Nugent.
	â€¢	Contributors should fork the repository before making any changes.

This ensures the project remains stable and all modifications are reviewed before entering the codebase.

Ways to Help
	â€¢	Report bugs (screenshots or logs preferred)
	â€¢	Improve documentation or spelling/grammar
	â€¢	Suggest support for additional hardware or compositors
	â€¢	Propose code cleanups or refactors

How to Submit a Pull Request
	1.	Fork the repository to your own GitHub account.
	2.	Create a feature branch in your fork.
	3.	Make your changes in small, focused commits.
	4.	If your change affects behaviour, update README.md or relevant docs.
	5.	Open a pull request against the main branch of this repository.
	6.	Wait for review. Only approved PRs will be merged.

